Hey team. Quick question: did the list of potential bases for FICs change after the introduction of the new recipe? I have almost 100k UICs waiting at MRZ17 and it hasn't been RNG'd for several weeks (if it's just bad luck, all good). But would be nice to know if that specific base is out of the list, so I can soak up the fuel cost/time and move those FICs to a different base. Thanks!

@SW4GN3R two rental features I'm surprised (not negatively, it just seems like a pivot from things previously said) are:

Pay over time (vs. prepay for a specific time period),Being able to cancel a rental,
Those features definitely favor the rentor vs. the asset holder.  I'm assuming that's why the shift was made?
